Preheat your #oven{} to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7. Trim the @aubergine{1} then
cut into roughly 2cm pieces. Pop the aubergine onto a lined #baking tray{}.

Drizzle with @sesame oil{40%ml}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then
toss to coat. Spread out in a single layer. When the oven is hot, roast on the
top shelf until the aubergine is soft and golden, ~{20-25%minutes}. Turn
halfway through.

Meanwhile, boil a large #pot{} of salted @water{to taste} for the pasta. When
boiling, add the @dried linguine{180%g} to the water and bring back to the boil.

Cook until softened, ~{12%minutes}. Once cooked, drain in a #colander{} and pop
back in the pot. Drizzle with @oil{to taste} and stir through to prevent sticking.
Cover to keep warm.

When the aubergine has been cooking for ~{8-10%minutes}, remove from the oven.
Pop the @cherry tomatoes{125%g} onto the same #baking tray{}. Drizzle with
@oil{to taste}, season with @salt{to taste} and @pepper{to taste} then pop back
into the oven for the remaining cooking time, ~{12-15%minutes}. Slice the
@lemon{1} into 4 wedges.

Meanwhile, place a #pan{} over medium-high heat with a very light drizzle of
@oil{to taste}. Once hot, cook the @tomato paste{1%tin} until fragrant,
~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the juice of two lemon wedges, 50ml water and @sugar{1/2%tsp}. Pour in
the @creme fraiche{125%g} and allow to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Season to
taste with salt, pepper and sugar.

> TIP: Loosen the sauce with a splash of water if necessary!

Once everything is ready, remove the aubergine and tomatoes from the oven. Toss
the linguine, aubergine and half the @grated Italian style hard cheese{50%g}
through the sauce, allowing everything to warm through.

Divide the aubergine linguine between #bowls{}. Garnish with blistered tomatoes,
lemon wedges and remaining @grated Italian style hard cheese{75%g}.